### JTS Topology Suite

*An open-source Java software library, for when the geometry of things actually matters.*

**Original author**: Martin Davis. A name etched in the digital ether, like a scar on a perfectly smooth surface.
• **Stable release**: 1.20.0 &#91;1&#93; – 30 August 2024. Fourteen months ago. Time marches on, relentlessly. Like a poorly rendered line segment.

**Repository**:
• github .com /locationtech /jts. A digital wasteland where code goes to live, or die. Whichever is less effort.

Written in [Java](/Java_(programming_language)). A language that’s seen better days, much like its users.
**Platform**: [Java SE](/Java_SE). The eternal stage for this particular drama.
**Type**: [Library](/Library_(computer_science)). A collection of tools. Useful, I suppose, if you have a problem that needs solving.
**License**: [Eclipse Public License](/Eclipse_Public_License) v.1.0 (starting with 1.15), [GNU Lesser General Public License](/GNU_Lesser_General_Public_License) (up to version 1.14). Because even code needs rules. And sometimes, those rules change. Like loyalties.

**Website**: locationtech .github .io /jts. The official pronouncements. The sanctioned truth.

